-- Softbank's Miyauchi to Be Willcom President in Reorganization, Nikkei Says
-- B y   Y o s h i a k i   N o h a r a
-- 2010-10-10T01:50:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/softbank-s-miyauchi-to-be-willcom-president-in-reorganization-nikkei-says.html
Ken Miyauchi, a Softbank Corp.
director, will become president of Willcom Inc., a PHS (personal
handy-phone system) carrier undergoing court-led restructuring
with help from Softbank, the Nikkei newspaper reported.  Miyauchi, 60, is chief operating officer of Softbank Mobile
Corp., the report said. The Softbank group will provide jobs to
Willcom employees made redundant, Willcom is expected to say in
a rehabilitation plan to be submitted to the Tokyo District
Court on Thursday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yoshiaki Nohara in Tokyo at 
 ynohara1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
